<section id="fb1">
  <p class="feedbacktext">It isn't possible to add the percentage of one group to that of another to reach a total in this way. In a proportional bar chart, the whole bar refers to one group only, but shows how different smaller values make up that whole.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p class="feedbacktext">These are the same figures as in the standard bar chart at the top, but presented as a proportional bar chart. The figures for each activity are built up, one on top of another, to reach a total percentage for the age group of 100 per cent.</p>
</section>

<section id="examtips">
<p class="popuptext">The information for the Writing Task in the previous exercise is presented as a standard bar chart. It could have been presented in a number of other ways, for example as pie charts or a proportional bar chart.</p>
